Saskatoon Freezing Deaths

They all sadly 
died from Hypothermia.
Book I recommend to learn more:

Starlight Tour 
The Last Lonely
 Night of Neil Stonechild.

stickerText:
Mission:
“Kill the Indian, Save the Man.”

They were 
abused/punished 
for expressing 
any form of 
cultural 
practice.

The kids were approximately 
between the ages 
of 4-16.
They forcibly removed these children from their homes & the parents weren’t able to do anything about it.

Many other 
traumatic
events took 
place in 
these 
schools.

Over 150,000 children attended. 
Thousands never made it home.
Last school closed down in 1996.
These type of schools also targeted the indigenous people of South America, Australia, New Zealand & more.

Movies to watch to get a more in depth look: 
•We Were Children 
•Indian Horse
•Rabbit Proof Fence
